    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, remove the base of your <strong>lettuce</strong></p><p>Wash the<strong> lettuce</strong> under <strong>cold running water</strong> and cut away the core, then pat dry with kitchen paper, and tear the<strong> lettuce leaves </strong>from the stem until you are left with a pile of leaves</p><p>Combine the juice of the <strong>remaining lemon</strong> in a bowl with a little drizzle of <strong>olive oil</strong> and your <strong>chopped dates </strong>– this is your<strong> lemon & date vinaigrette</strong></p>",
